<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-04-06T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-04-06T13:00:00-05:00" n="1454" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1454">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72114/359</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-04-06T18:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1915, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 8 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1891. <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> again asks
                            me to have telegraphic assurance conveyed to <persName>Gerard</persName>
                            for the German Government of the acceptance <hi rend="italic">in
                                toto</hi> by His Majesty’s Government of the scheme put forward <pb facs="1275" n="1017" xml:id="pg_1017"/> by the German Government in
                            connection with the inspection of camps where British civilian: and war
                            prisoners are interned in Germany.</p>
                        <p>
                            <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> asks the favor of
                            a telegraphic reply from <persName>Gerard</persName> assuring him that
                            the British Government’s assent is understood.<note n="1" xml:id="d1454fn1">Transmitted to the Ambassador in Germany, April 7,
                                No. 1479.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>